\begin_inset Formula $x\geq0$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
This code is barely stable enough to pass all test cases in netlib problems if we perturb 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 by 
\begin_inset Formula $c+\varepsilon1$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon$
\end_inset

 is some tiny positive number.
 This avoids the issue that the set of optimal points can be unbounded.
 All examples are solved in 70 iterations,
 most of them solved in 40 iterations.
 (for 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{-6}$
